### SnapFuel Backend Test Suite (Success Patterns Only)
### Usage: VS Code REST Client extension
### Run top-to-bottom in order.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@contentType = application/json
@sponsorWallet = 0x1111111111111111111111111111111111111111

### 0) Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 1) OpenAPI YAML
GET {{baseUrl}}/.well-known/openapi.yaml

### 2) Privacy page
GET {{baseUrl}}/privacy

### 3) Create profile
# @name createProfile
POST {{baseUrl}}/profiles
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "creator.normal@example.com",
  "region": "JP",
  "roles": ["developer", "creator"],
  "tools_used": ["scraping", "design"],
  "attributes": {
    "plan": "starter",
    "source": "http-test"
  }
}

### 4) List profiles
GET {{baseUrl}}/profiles
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 5) Register user (alias endpoint)
# @name registerUser
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "registered.normal@example.com",
  "region": "US",
  "roles": ["builder"],
  "tools_used": ["storage"]
}

### 6) Create campaign
# @name createCampaign
POST {{baseUrl}}/campaigns
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Normal Campaign",
  "sponsor": "ACME",
  "sponsor_wallet_address": "{{sponsorWallet}}",
  "target_roles": ["developer"],
  "target_tools": ["scraping", "design"],
  "required_task": "Share email address",
  "subsidy_per_call_cents": 5,
  "budget_cents": 1000,
  "query_urls": ["https://example.com/search?q=campaign"]
}

### 7) List campaigns
GET {{baseUrl}}/campaigns
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 8) List campaigns filtered by sponsor wallet
GET {{baseUrl}}/campaigns?sponsor_wallet_address={{sponsorWallet}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 9) Get campaign by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.$.campaign.id}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 10) Campaign discovery list
GET {{baseUrl}}/campaigns/discovery
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 11) Complete task
# @name completeTask
POST {{baseUrl}}/tasks/complete
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "campaign_id": "{{createCampaign.response.body.$.campaign.id}}",
  "user_id": "{{createProfile.response.body.$.id}}",
  "task_name": "Share email address",
  "details": "{\"email\":\"creator.normal@example.com\"}"
}

### 12) Sponsor dashboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/dashboard/sponsor/{{createCampaign.response.body.$.campaign.id}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 13) Record creator metric event
POST {{baseUrl}}/creator/metrics/event
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "skill_name": "scraping",
  "platform": "web",
  "event_type": "completed",
  "duration_ms": 1300,
  "success": true
}

### 14) Read creator metrics summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/creator/metrics
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 15) Prometheus metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/metrics

### Notes
### - This file intentionally excludes paid-path endpoints:
###   /tool/{service}/run, /proxy/{service}/run, /sponsored-apis (create/run)
###   because they require x402 payment setup or specific sponsor-budget preconditions.
### - If you want, I can create a second paid-flow test file with the required headers/envs.
